1. Primitive Data Type
      Integer  >> 4 byte of memory space >> -2147483648 to 2147483647 
      Character >> 1 byte >> -128 to 127 or 0 to 255
      Boolean  >>  true or false
      Float Point >> 4 bytes >>
      Double Floating Point >> 8 bytes
      Valueless or Void >> no value
      Wide Character >> representation -- wchar_t >> 2 or 4 bytes long 

2. Derived Data Type
      Function
      Array
      Pointer
      Reference 

3. Abstract or user-defined Data Type
      Class
      Structure
      Union
      Enumeration
      Typedef defined Data type




      